item.title: Pebble Time Round
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Meet the show stopper. Pebble Time Round is the smartwatch that’s just as beautiful as it is functional. You’ll never miss that call or text again, even when your phone is buried in your bag. With a classic round design, built-in microphone, and a slew of loved Pebble features, you’ll always be in the know without compromising style or fit. Did we mention it’s the lightest and thinnest smartwatch, ever?! Good. It’s pretty gorgeous, too.
item.excerpt:encoded: Pebble Health–track your stepss Always-on, color e-paper display Quick-charging–just 15 minutes

item.title: Pebble Classic
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Classic was our first. It captured the hearts of over a million consumers and set the tone for wearing cool tech right on your wrist. Made to fit your busy, active lifestyle, Classic boasts everything you need in a smartwatch–notifications, thousands of apps, water resistance and up to 7 days of battery life–in the original look and feel. It’s the watch that broke the Kickstarter record and sparked the smartwatch craze. ‘Nuff said.

item.title: HPE ProLiant BL660c Gen9 Server Blade
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Do you need a server blade designed to scale for your data-intensive workloads? The HPE ProLiant BL660c Gen9 Server Blade is ideal for virtualization, database, business processing, and other four processor (4P) applications where fine-tuning of data center space and price/performance is paramount. Focused on flexibility, it offers more storage options, faster I/O, and more powerful processing to meet any workload needs at a low TCO.
All of this is managed by HPE OneView, the converged management platform that accelerates IT service delivery and boosts business performance. Supporting the Intel® Xeon® E5-4600 v3 or v4 processors, the BL660c Gen9 Server Blade redefines density-optimized 4-socket blade technology without compromising on performance.
HPE DDR4 SmartMemory offers up to a 33% 1 performance increase from our previous generation. Additional support includes support for 2 NVMe SSDs, tiered array controller options, 12 Gb/s SAS, 20 Gb FlexibleLOM NICs, M.2, and USB 3.0.
item.excerpt:encoded: The HPE ProLiant BL660c Gen9 Server Blade delivers four socket (4S) computing in a single-wide, full-height form factor. It has support for two or four cost-effective Intel Xeon E5-4600 v3 or v4 processors each with up to 22 cores and 135 watts without system configuration restrictions.

item.title: HP Onboard Administrator
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This BladeSystem feature provides: Wizards for simple, fast setup and configuration, highly available and secure access to the HP BladeSystem infrastructure, security roles for server, network, and storage administrators, agent-less device health and status and thermal Logic power and cooling information and control. Each enclosure is shipped with one Onboard Administrator module/firmware.
If desired, a customer may order a second redundant Onboard Administrator module for each enclosure. When two Onboard Administrator modules are present in a BladeSystem c-Class enclosure, they work in an active - standby mode, assuring full redundancy with integrated management.
item.excerpt:encoded: The HP Onboard Administrator for the HP BladeSystem enclosures is the intelligence of the c-Class infrastructure. Together with the enclosure's display (HP Insight Display), the Onboard Administrator has been designed for both local and remote administration of HP BladeSystem c-Class enclosures.

item.title: HPE ProLiant WS460c Gen9 Graphics Server Blade
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Do you need workstation-class high performance graphics and an improved end-user experience for their virtual desktops? Would you like to gain the security and manageability benefits of a data center architecture? The HPE ProLiant WS460c Gen9 Graphics Server Blade allows you to centralize your organization’s high-end desktop PCs and workstations for more business efficient end-user computing infrastructure while delivering the same superior user experience. Assisted with workstation-class high-performance graphics hardware, the server blade can be a single-user dedicated graphics server or host multiple users sharing resources through graphics virtualization.
item.excerpt:encoded: With virtualized GPU technology from NVIDIA® and AMD ®, right sizing the GPU performance to its user needs is a breeze through simple software configuration. The HPE ProLiant WS460c Gen9 Graphics Server Blade is your high-performance end-user computing platform delivering superior user experience from the data center.

item.title: HP ProLiant WS460c Gen8 Graphics Server Blade
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Do you need centralized, end-user desktop computing delivered from the data center with workstation-class high performance graphics? Would you like to gain the security and manageability of the data center and lose the high cost per user of most workstations? The HP ProLiant WS460c Gen8 Graphics Server Blade allows you to centralize your organization’s workstation at a lower cost per seat and with the performance your users expect. The computing power in the form of a graphics server blade is located in the data center where it can be more easily, securely, and economically managed.
The results are improved uptime and business continuity, enhanced data center security, and reduced IT costs. This graphics server blade has comprehensive graphics acceleration capabilities for VDI, and provides up to 60% cost reduction per seat compared to previous generation configurations.
Additionally, the up-to-3X improvement in user density saves data center power, space, and management time.
